node.text: This video stole my heart! Children & young people living in conflict are using poetry to call for peace! I'm so proud to team up with @UNICEF to share these powerful, emotive poems. As the world battles #COVID19, peace in countries affected by conflict is more critical than ever. UNICEF’s Poems for Peace provides a platform for children and young people affected by conflict to express themselves and have their voices heard, often for the first time. I'm committing now and in the future to providing these young poets around the world a place to have their voices heard. We hear you guys and we love you! #ChildrenUnderAttack #PoemsForPeace #WorldPoetryDay

"Slowly their love healed her, and made her scars feel beautiful." We are all healing from something in our lives…relationships, breakups, loss, parents, accidents, mistakes. Healing is human. It brings us together. I’m constantly trying to heal from old wounds. Like trying to heal the scared little boy I was growing up. Hold his hand and make him feel safe and loved. It’s not always easy, but time fights for us all to heal. What are you healing from? 

I loved working with my friend @findingxfletcher on this, go stream her new song "Healing."
